HTML ELEMENT->
An html element is an individual component of an html document or a web once it has been parsed
Its is an building block of html
    it has an opening tag
    it may or may not have closing tag

Elements with no closing tags are as follow:
   <hr>
   <br>
   <img>
   <input>
   <link>
   <meta>

Use of meta tag in HTML:

    Definition and Usage:

Metadata is data (information) about data.
The <meta> tag provides metadata about the HTML document. Metadata will not be displayed on the page, but will be machine parsable.
Meta elements are typically used to specify page description, keywords, author of the document, last modified, and other metadata.
The metadata can be used by browsers (how to display content or reload page), search engines (keywords), or other web services.

     UTF-8 Meaning: 

UTF-8 (8-bit Unicode Transformation Format) is a variable width character encoding capable of encoding all 1,112,064[nb 1]
valid code points in Unicode using one to four 8-bit bytes.

